claim: Cell- and egg-based flu vaccines have the potential to develop mutations during production, which may reduce their effectiveness.
explanation: A table listing vaccine presentation (Single-Dose Prefilled Syringe), the carton NDC number (49281-724-10), and components with their NDC numbers, followed by storage and handling instructions (temperature range, do not freeze, protect from light, expiration guidance). The image provides NDC identifiers and storage/handling instructions only and contains no information about cell- or egg-based production, potential mutations, or effects on vaccine effectiveness, so it does not support the claim.
